Bauchi State Commissioner of Finance and Economic Development Garba Sarki Akuyam has resigned his appointment as Commissioner and member of the state executive council. He disclosed his resignation at a Press Conference on Friday. The Commissioner said that recent developments and political realities in Bauchi State were the main reasons of his resignation. Akuyam said that, he served the administration in the state as Commissioner of Rural Development, Commissioner of Finance and Director General APC state campaign organization in the last four years.  ” Therefore, it is my privilege and singular honour to most sincerely register my appreciations for recognition accorded me by your Excellency to serve your Government and the good people of Bauchi state as commissioner, promising to answer another call to serve my dear state when ever called upon to do that in another capacity as the need may perhaps arise”. He said. He added that he tendered his resignation after wide consultation with family, friends and associates. He said that he has already delivered his letter of resignation to Governor Mohammed Abubakar through the Secretary to the State Government (SSG) . Bayelsa Commissioner resigns page 4 Commissioner dares Amosun, resigns to battle governor's candidate